# Template: copy to deploy/server.env (gitignored) and fill in.
# This file is the production-oriented env on disk (sometimes called "env.prod" informally).
#
# Used by:
# - `./start.sh --prepare` (loads web/.env + this file; validates LLM + build; does not start Node)
# - `npm run deploy:node` (scp to remote as server.env; remote sources it before build)
# - Optional: DEPLOY_LOAD_SERVER_ENV=1 with static deploy-webplace.sh
# - Optional: DEPLOY_PUSH_SERVER_ENV=1 to copy this next to static out/
#
# Tutor needs `next start` (see `npm run build:server` + `npm run start:server`). Static-only out/ has no /api/chat.

# --- Process / nginx (scripts/start-server-stripped.mjs)
# Listen address for start-server-stripped.mjs (process.env.HOSTNAME).
# If public nginx runs in Docker (e.g. nginx_global) and proxies to the host via 172.17.0.1, bind:
#   HOSTNAME=0.0.0.0
# If nginx on the same OS without that hop, loopback is enough:
#   HOSTNAME=127.0.0.1
# Must match nginx proxy_pass and DEPLOY_NODE_PORT when using deploy-node.sh:
# PORT=34827
# Do not set NODE_ENV=production in this file if you run npm ci on the same host (skips devDependencies).
# Use NODE_ENV=production in the start command (pm2/systemd), e.g. NODE_ENV=production npm run start:server

# LLM API base URL (no trailing slash). Must be reachable FROM THIS HOST (the Node process).
#
# Do NOT use 127.0.0.1 on a cloud VM unless you run the SSH reverse tunnel from mini62
# (see ITCS/featureLLM/docs/MANUAL_INTEGRACAO.md § 1.1, paragraph on itcsVM).
#
# Typical choices (same manual § 1.1):
#   A — Public HTTPS (servers outside Tailscale, e.g. itcsVM): https://llm.webplace.cc
#   B — Tailscale direct to Mac mini: http://<tailnet-ip>:28471  (confirm with tailscale ip -4 on Mac)
#   Local Mac + Docker API on same machine: http://127.0.0.1:28471
LLM_API_URL=https://llm.webplace.cc

# Same Bearer as ITCS/featureLLM/.env — never commit deploy/server.env.
LLM_API_TOKEN=

# Optional — forwarded by Next /api/chat to POST /edu/chat (see featureLLM docs/EDU_API_CONTRACT.md):
# Omit both → request has no "model" field → API default is usually "fast" (lower latency).
# LLM_EDU_CHAT_MODEL=smart
# LLM_EDU_CHAT_MODEL_RETRY=smart

# On the API host (featureLLM .env), not here: EDU_CHAT_NUM_PREDICT=384 for shorter generations, etc.

# Optional: path to rag_knowledge on the ingest machine (npm run ingest:rag).
# RAG_SOURCES_PATH=
